Hi Jeff,

I have included results on hexapods and quadrupeds with two degrees of
freedom per joint in my GECCO 2008 paper.  The controllers in that
paper were evolved with fixed hand-designed symmetries, and they
generalized well to the more complex robots, producing regular,
animal-like gaits.  In my most recent work that I will present at this
year&#39;s GECCO, the emphasis is on evolving the symmetry of the
controller on difficult terrains such as inclined ground where the
appropriate symmetry is unknown.  I have not yet studied more complex
robots with this symmetry evolution approach, but I certainly plan to
do it.

Vinod


